=============================
=      File description     =
=============================
this exercise contains the following java classes:
Book - This class represents a book, which has a title, author, year of publication and different literary
    aspects.
Patron - This class represents a library patron that has a name and assigns values to different literary
    aspects of books.
Library - This class represents a library, which hold a collection of books. Patrons can register at the
    library to be able to check out books, if a copy of the requested book is available.

=============================
=          Design           =
=============================
Book- I used the skeleton file from the moodle.
Patron- I used the given API.
Library- I used the given API.

=============================
=  Implementation details   =
=============================
In the Library class I added 2 public members- bookArray- which is an array of all books in the library,
and patronArray- which is an array of all the patrons in the library. I also added a method books_at_patron-
that counts the amount of books the given patron (using patron ID) is borrowing.

